This paper belongs to the field of computer security and network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the application of machine learning algorithms to improve the performance of the Snort IDS, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the development of the Snort adaptive plug-in involves software engineering practices, which could fall under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
